{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_112","type":"agent_message","text":"Implemented the DOCX export pipeline fix set and left a checkpoint commit at `4906f99` (`feat(prompt-81): docx export pipeline`).\n\nThe substantive changes were:\n- split canonical manuscript vs DOCX export in hydration/snapshot state so the finalize reader keeps using text, while DOCX is exposed separately as `latest_story_export_asset`\n- supersede stale `story_docx` assets when accepted story text changes, so exports stay tied to the current manuscript\n- add `POST /api/v1/sessions/{session_id}/artifacts/story-docx` to explicitly generate or refresh the export and return asset metadata\n- align action policy so chat-driven Word downloads are allowed when manuscript text is ready, even before a DOCX asset record exists\n- update targeted backend/frontend tests for regeneration, hydration, policy, and the new route\n\nVerification:\n- `pytest backend/tests/test_story_export_service.py backend/tests/test_session_api.py backend/tests/test_session_hydration_service.py backend/tests/test_action_policy_service.py` → `62 passed`\n- `ruff check ...` on touched backend files → passed\n- `python -m compileall backend/app` → passed\n- `npm --prefix frontend run build` → passed\n- `npm --prefix frontend run test -- src/features/session/sessionArtifacts.test.ts src/pages/session/SessionWorkspacePage.test.tsx` → `34 passed`\n- No browser/screenshot checks were run because this was a backend/export contract change, not a visual UI change.\n\nThe required reviewer summary was written last at [summary.md](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/.yolopilot/runs/20260331T205548_storyteller_prompt_pack/81_word_document_export_pipeline/summary.md)."}}
